theorem Topology.interiorClosure_iter8_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Reduce the innermost seven-fold nest using the existing lemma.
  have h₁ :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_iter7_idempotent (A := A)
  -- Apply one more `interior ∘ closure` pair to both sides of `h₁`.
  have h₂ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure
        (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
          (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))))))) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    simpa using
      congrArg (fun S : Set X =>
        interior (closure (interior (closure S)))) h₁
  -- Simplify the right-hand side with the basic idempotence lemma.
  have h₃ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent (A := A)
  simpa [h₃] using h₂

theorem Topology.closureInteriorClosure_eq_closure_of_isOpen_set
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    have hSub : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono hSub
  ·
    have hIncl : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X)) hA
    exact closure_mono hIncl

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_mono_of_closure_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (h : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (B : Set X)) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := by
  exact interior_mono h
